{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isCancelled"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After the value of this property becomes ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", it remains ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" indefinitely.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There is no way to uncancel a task.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This property returns the actual cancellation state of the task, regardless of whether","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a cancellation shield is active. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task/isCancelled"},{"text":" (the static property)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you need cancellation checking that respects active shields.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Instance property isCancelled ignores Task Cancellation Shields","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Instance-property-isCancelled-ignores-Task-Cancellation-Shields"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The instance property ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task.isCancelled"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is not contextual and therefore does not respect cancellation shields. If a task","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was cancelled and is executing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with an active cancellation shield, this property will return the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"actual","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cancellation status of the specific task.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is possible to determine if a shield is active and then actively determine","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the cancelled status should be temporarily ignored by using this pair of APIs:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["withUnsafeCurrentTask { unsafeTask in","  if unsafeTask.hasActiveCancellationShield {","    false","  } else {","    unsafeTask.isCancelled","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which is equivalent to the contextually aware static ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task.isCancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["// Contextually aware, and equivalent to the snippet using UnsafeCurrentTask:","Task.isCancelled"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Prefer using ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task.isCancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (the static property) in most situations when checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the cancellation status from inside the task.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"See Also","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task/isCancelled"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"See Also","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Task/checkCancellation()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"See Also","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Task/hasActiveCancellationShield","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":